classes.name: PythonLexer
classes.docstring:
For Python source code (version 3.x).

.. versionchanged:: 2.5
   This is now the default ``PythonLexer``.  It is still available as the
   alias ``Python3Lexer``.

classes.name: Python2Lexer
classes.docstring:
For Python 2.x source code.

.. versionchanged:: 2.5
   This class has been renamed from ``PythonLexer``.  ``PythonLexer`` now
   refers to the Python 3 variant.  File name patterns like ``*.py`` have
   been moved to Python 3 as well.

classes.name: PythonConsoleLexer
classes.docstring:
For Python console output or doctests, such as:

.. sourcecode:: pycon

    >>> a = 'foo'
    >>> print(a)
    foo
    >>> 1 / 0
    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File "<stdin>", line 1, in <module>
    ZeroDivisionError: integer division or modulo by zero

Additional options:

`python3`
    Use Python 3 lexer for code.  Default is ``True``.

    .. versionadded:: 1.0
    .. versionchanged:: 2.5
       Now defaults to ``True``.

classes.name: PythonTracebackLexer
classes.docstring:
For Python 3.x tracebacks, with support for chained exceptions.

.. versionchanged:: 2.5
   This is now the default ``PythonTracebackLexer``.  It is still available
   as the alias ``Python3TracebackLexer``.

classes.name: Python2TracebackLexer
classes.docstring:
For Python tracebacks.

.. versionchanged:: 2.5
   This class has been renamed from ``PythonTracebackLexer``.
   ``PythonTracebackLexer`` now refers to the Python 3 variant.

classes.name: CythonLexer
classes.docstring: For Pyrex and Cython source code.

classes.name: DgLexer
classes.docstring:
Lexer for dg,
a functional and object-oriented programming language
running on the CPython 3 VM.

classes.name: NumPyLexer
classes.docstring: A Python lexer recognizing Numerical Python builtins.
